    {
      "id": "p001",
      "index": 1,
      "source": "To double the scale-up bandwidth using copper interconnect, NVIDIA would have to achieve a per lane bandwidth of 448Gbit/s uni-di (and implemented with simulatanous bi-directional SerDes so that each physical channel carries 448G of RX and 448G of TX). However, this is a challenging feat as they would first have to prove the feasibility of 448Gb/s PAM4 SerDes at large volumes, then implement echo cancellation to achieve bidirectional bandwidth, which is in itself extremely difficult. We believe Nvidia is going for 448G uni-di only.",
      "source_html": null,
      "element_type": "p",
      "inline_elements": [
        {
          "type": "link",
          "text": "echo cancellation to achieve bidirectional bandwidth",
          "start": 395,
          "end": 447,
          "href": "https://newsletter.semianalysis.com/p/vera-rubin-extreme-co-design-an-evolution",
          "title": null,
          "span_id": "LINK_1"
        }
      ],
      "parent_block_id": "b0186",
      "parent_block_index": 186,
      "parent_block_type": "p",
      "parent_block_markdown": "To double the scale-up bandwidth using copper interconnect, NVIDIA would have to achieve a per lane bandwidth of 448Gbit/s uni-di (and implemented with simulatanous bi-directional SerDes so that each physical channel carries 448G of RX and 448G of TX). However, this is a challenging feat as they would first have to prove the feasibility of 448Gb/s PAM4 SerDes at large volumes, then implement [echo cancellation to achieve bidirectional bandwidth](https://newsletter.semianalysis.com/p/vera-rubin-extreme-co-design-an-evolution), which is in itself extremely difficult. We believe Nvidia is going for 448G uni-di only.",
      "parent_block_plain_text": "To double the scale-up bandwidth using copper interconnect, NVIDIA would have to achieve a per lane bandwidth of 448Gbit/s uni-di (and implemented with simulatanous bi-directional SerDes so that each physical channel carries 448G of RX and 448G of TX). However, this is a challenging feat as they would first have to prove the feasibility of 448Gb/s PAM4 SerDes at large volumes, then implement echo cancellation to achieve bidirectional bandwidth, which is in itself extremely difficult. We believe Nvidia is going for 448G uni-di only.",
      "parent_source_html": null,
      "parent_inline_elements": [
        {
          "type": "link",
          "text": "echo cancellation to achieve bidirectional bandwidth",
          "start": 395,
          "end": 447,
